uter regions of the super-Eddington disc/wind\ncan explain the luminosity-temperature behaviour, but are difficult to\nreconcile with the lack of strong variability at higher energies, assuming this\nemission arises from the most compact regions. Instead, we may be seeing\nevidence for further radial stratification of the accretion flow than is\nincluded in the simple models considered, with a combination of winds and\nadvection resulting in the suppressed high-energy variability.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Nov 2019 17:30:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Apr 2020 11:19:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-06"}
