trols a\ngeneralised flop-flop autoequivalence. These results both recover and extend\nDonovan-Wemyss's. I give concrete applications and computations in the case of\npartial resolutions of Kleinian singularities, where the classical contraction\nalgebra becomes inadequate.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Nov 2019 17:35:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-22"}
