ng or deposition at elevated temperatures and\ndispersing bands are observed by angle resolved photoemission spectroscopy.\nBoth electron-like and hole-like bands are evident for the\n($\\sqrt{3}$$\\times$$\\sqrt{3}$)R30$^{\\circ}$ phase, while a nearly free\nelectron-like parabolic surface state is observed for the\np(3$\\times$3)R15$^{\\circ}$ phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Nov 2019 12:33:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 6 Dec 2019 13:54:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
